<body>
    <h1>Overview</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>Ascension Health Alliance=E2=80=99s IAM is a strategic program t=
o streamline identity access governance to enhance overall security and com=
pliance posture of Ascension Health Alliance. The program consists of effic=
ient execution of the following tasks:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Onboard Ascension Health Alliance Associates and NEP users to SailPoint =
IdentityIQ IAM platform.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Streamline users accounts and access management for downstream applicati=
on systems to improve overall efficiency.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Establish associates LCM processes for pre-hire, new-hire, mover, termin=
ation, suspension, leave of absence, re-hire, profile update, conversion, s=
econdary work relationship provisioning, secondary work relationship suspen=
sion and secondary work relationship termination.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Establish NEP LCM processes for new-hire, mover, termination, suspension=
, leave of absence, re-hire, profile update, conversion, secondary work rel=
ationship provisioning, secondary work relationship suspension and secondar=
y work relationship termination.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Establish LCM process for Non-Worker users onboarding and offboarding/te=
rmination.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Integration of various enterprise applications (Active Directory (42 dom=
ains), ServiceNow, UKG, Oracle ERP Cloud, Oracle EPM Cloud, OCI) with the I=
AM platform to enable their access governance via the central IAM platform.=
&nbsp;</p></li>
</ul>
<p></p>
<p>IAM processes such as onboarding new user accounts, managing internal tr=
ansitions, and terminating access, form the foundation of Ascension Health =
Alliance=E2=80=99s identity governance framework. Current IAM processes req=
uire manual intervention, resulting in delayed access provisioning and revo=
cation. This is a compliance risk and impacts the organization's overall se=
curity.</p>
<p>This initiative is dedicated to establishing an efficient IT control fra=
mework for Ascension Health Alliance applications centered around Identity =
and Access Management solutions. This initiative supports the creation of a=
 secure IT environment and prioritizes immediate requirements while continu=
ously enhancing the IAM solution to align with Ascension Health Alliance=E2=
=80=99s desired future state.</p>
<p></p>
<p></p>
    </div>
</body>
